question: Show payment trends over time
sql: SELECT DATE_FORMAT(p.created_date, '%Y-%m') AS month, SUM(p.trans_amount_decimal) AS total_revenue FROM subscription_payment_details p WHERE p.created_date >= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE, INTERVAL 12 MONTH) GROUP BY month ORDER BY month ASC

question: Show payment trends over time
sql: SELECT DATE_FORMAT(p.created_date, '%Y-%m-01') AS month, SUM(p.trans_amount_decimal) AS revenue FROM subscription_payment_details p WHERE p.status = 'ACTIVE' GROUP BY month ORDER BY month ASC

question: Number of subscriptions between 1 may 2025 and 31 may 2025
sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) as num_subscriptions 
FROM subscription_contract_v2 
WHERE DATE(subcription_start_date) BETWEEN '2025-05-01' AND '2025-05-31'

question: Revenue between 1 april 2025 and 30 april 2025
sql:
SELECT SUM(p.trans_amount_decimal) as total_revenue, COUNT(*) as num_payments
FROM subscription_payment_details p
WHERE DATE(p.created_date) BETWEEN '2025-04-01' AND '2025-04-30' 
AND p.status = 'ACTIVE'

question: number of subscribers with more than 5 subscriptions and who have done more than 5 payme
sql:
SELECT 'More than 5 Subscriptions' as category, COUNT(*) as value 
FROM (SELECT merchant_user_id FROM subscription_contract_v2 GROUP BY merchant_user_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 5) t1
UNION ALL
SELECT 'More than 5 Subscriptions' as category, COUNT(*) as value  
FROM (SELECT merchant_user_id FROM subscription_contract_v2 GROUP BY merchant_user_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 5) t2
